Get a few facts straight.
<br />

<br />
The UN (actually, the British, who had the place after WWII) did not GIVE the jews anything.  Jews moved to a desert that no one wanted and no country claimed and BOUGHT the land, paying outrageous prices in most cases.  It was a Zionist movement to reestablish Israel, and it worked.  On the contrary, the British, and then the UN, did their best to block jewish immigration, and the formation of Israel.
<br />

<br />
THERE NEVER WAS A PALASTINE!  No such organized country has ever existed.  The term has been used to identify a geographc area, but was never a country, people, or government.  The concept of a Palastinian nation is recent, within the last decade or two, and is a blatent copying of the Zionist movement, which movement "Palastinians" deplore, lol.
