				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">You might be surprised by my answer on this.  In spite of overwhelming force from the Arabs, Israel established and has maintained a state since 1949.  They have conquered and administered the West Bank and Gaza.  This historical event is fact.
<br />

<br />
A fact prophesied by the Tanak among the prophecies of Isaiah, Ezekiel, Daniel, and the "minor" prophets.  That prophecy includes the gathering of Jews from all parts of the world...including unlikely places like Cush (present-day Ethiopia).
<br />

<br />
There is no other nation that has literally been reformed from all parts of the world back into its original geographic region ever.  That hints at something invisible going on.
<br />

<br />
I do not believe that the present day Israelis own the moral high ground, however.  They have used every ploy possible to frustrate the ambitions of the Palestinian Arabs...and the surrounding Arabs in turn.  They have created what can only be viewed as a deep, abiding enmity with their closest geographical neighbors.  It wasn't surprising, therefore, that Israel has put out feelers for joining the European Union...because it is difficult to imagine normal relations between Israel and Syria, Saudi Arabia, or even US-backed Iraq.  BUT...the peace with Egypt and with Jordan still holds.
<br />

<br />
There is more eschatology that I could discuss here, but I suspect that attempting to discuss it isn't worth the ridicule...so I won't.  Just something to consider.
<br />

<br />
Wolen<span class="gensmall"></span>


